text.section:
"Fiduciary" includes:
A trustee;
An executor or executrix;
A personal representative;
A receiver;
A special administrator;
A guardian;
A conservator;
A committee;
A custodian under the Maryland Uniform Transfers to Minors Act; and
Any other person who has a fiduciary relationship the responsibilities of which are customarily performed by a corporate fiduciary.

"Successor fiduciary" means a corporate fiduciary that is substituted for another corporate fiduciary under the provisions of § 15-1A-02 of this subtitle, by reason of:
A merger or consolidation of corporate fiduciaries;
The acquisition of the stock or assets of a corporate fiduciary by another corporate fiduciary;
The transfer by a corporate fiduciary of its trust and fiduciary business to another corporate fiduciary; or
The acquisition or formation by a corporate fiduciary of a subsidiary, which is itself a corporate fiduciary, in order to undertake the trust and fiduciary business of the subsidiary's parent entity.
